dice''''' was a [[France|French]] [[List of submarines of France|submarine]], one of nine of the {{Sclass-|Daphné|submarine|4}}.
On 4 March 1970, while diving in calm seas off [[Cape Camarat]] in the [[Mediterranean]], {{convert|35|mi}} east of [[Toulon]], a geophysical laboratory picked up the shock waves of an underwater explosion. French and Italian search teams found an oil slick and a few bits of debris, including a part that bore the name ''Eurydice''.
The cause of the explosion was never determined. All 57 crew were lost.
